HEADWORD: Bushment
<hw>Bush"ment</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>busshement</ets> ambush, fr. <ets>bush</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A thicket; a cluster of bushes.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An ambuscade.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir
